2018-09-24T18:21:20Z\u0022 title=\u002209/24/2018 06:21  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 24, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Tyko\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-26T11:41:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry, bribes won\u0027t help in this case \u003Cspan\u003E:-)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpecifically, the earlier patch\u00A0 was actually looked at by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57838-triggerau/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257838\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57838-triggerau/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@TriggerAu\u003C/a\u003E, and it has problems.\u00A0 Also, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57838-triggerau/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257838\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57838-triggerau/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@TriggerAu\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0is still around, and unless he asks me, I\u0027m not going to touch any of his mods.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/142910-aelfhe1m/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022142910\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/142910-aelfhe1m/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Aelfhe1m\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0can revisit his changes and figure out the issues.\u00A0 At the least, he should be able to recompile them for 1.4\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nivee~","CreatedById":183478,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-24T15:22:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am sorry for reviving this thread, but I have a real bad issue with Kronometer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is the settings.cfg:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003EKronometer\n{\n\tuseHomeDay = false\n\tuseHomeYear = false\n\tuseLeapYears = false\n\tCustomTime\n\t{\n\t\tSecond\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tsingular = Second\n \t\t\tplural = Seconds\n\t\t\tsymbol = s\n\t\t\tvalue = 1\n\t\t}\n\t\tMinute\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tsingular = Minute\n\t\t\tplural = Minutes\n\t\t\tsymbol = m\n\t\t\tvalue = 60\n\t\t}\n\t\tHour\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tsingular = Hour\n\t\t\tplural = Hours\n\t\t\tsymbol = h\n\t\t\tvalue = 3600\n\t\t}\n\t\tDay\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tsingular = Day\n\t\t\tplural = Days\n\t\t\tsymbol = d\n\t\t\tvalue = 86400\n\t\t}\n\t\tYear\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tsingular = Year\n\t\t\tplural = Years\n\t\t\tsymbol = y\n\t\t\tvalue = 31536000\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tDisplayDate\n\t{\n\t\tPrintDate\n\t\t{\n\t\t\toffsetTime = 0\n\t\t\toffsetDay = 1\n\t\t\toffsetYear = 1\n\t\t\tdisplayDate = \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;Y1\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;Y\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E, \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;D1\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;D\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\t\tdisplayTime = \u0026lt; - \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;H\u0026gt;\u0026lt;H0\u0026gt;\u0026lt;M\u0026gt;\u0026lt;M0\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\t\tdisplaySeconds = , \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;S\u0026gt;\u0026lt;S0\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\t}\n\t\tPrintDateNew\n\t\t{\n\t\t\toffsetTime = 0\n\t\t\toffsetDay = 1\n\t\t\toffsetYear = 1\n\t\t\tdisplayDate = \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;Y1\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;Y\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E, \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;D1\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;D\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\t\tdisplayTime = \u0026lt; - \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;H:D2\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;M:D2\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\t\tdisplaySeconds = :\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;S:D2\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\t}\n\t\tPrintDateCompact\n\t\t{\n\t\t\toffsetTime = 0\n\t\t\toffsetDay = 1\n\t\t\toffsetYear = 1\n\t\t\tdisplayDate = \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;Y0\u0026gt;\u0026lt;Y\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E, \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;D0\u0026gt;\u0026lt;D:00\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\t\tdisplayTime = , \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;H\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;M:00\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\t\tdisplaySeconds = :\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022tag\u0022\u003E\u0026lt;S:00\u0026gt;\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe cfg clearly states the duration of days and year in seconds, but in-game, one day is equal to 12 hours! How do I rectify it??\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"komodo","CreatedById":102065,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-24T18:11:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223546446\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161218\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551021740\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183478\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nivee~\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Nivee~ said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E cfg clearly states the duration of days and year in sec\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Eonds, but in-game, one day is equal to 12 hours! How do I rectify it?\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E?\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis doesn\u0027t set the length of a day for your planet, this defines what an hour is.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou want something like daylengthmultiplier if using sigma dimensions, or however you are rescaling, but in their respective configs.\u00A0That is what controls the actual physics.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Slverfox94739","CreatedById":196418,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-25T19:53:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m using SSRSS and Kronometer ingame the days are set to 8 hours. Is there a way to tweak the settings in kronometer so 24 hours goes by each day?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-03-25T22:42:14Z\u0022 title=\u002203/25/2019 10:42  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 25, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Slverfox94739\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OhioBob","CreatedById":128005,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-26T00:50:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223568472\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161218\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221553543584\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196418\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Slverfox94739\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Slverfox94739 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m using SSRSS and Kronometer ingame the days are set to 8 hours. Is there a way to tweak the settings in kronometer so 24 hours goes by each day?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the best option is to set the clock to 24 hours in the game settings, and not use Kronometer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe main reason to use Kronometer is when the day is neither 6 nor 24 hours.\u00A0 But when you want a 6- or 24-hour day, those options are available in the standard game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-03-26T00:52:44Z\u0022 title=\u002203/26/2019 12:52  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 26, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by OhioBob\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Slverfox94739","CreatedById":196418,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-26T01:16:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I don\u0027t use\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003EKronometer is does go to a 24 our clock. But the Sun\u00A0sets and rises 3 times during\u00A0that period (SSRSS has a ~8 hour day). I know it\u00A0just cosmetic, But I was trying to find a way use the 24 hour colck but only have the Sun rise/set once.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OhioBob","CreatedById":128005,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-26T05:18:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223568717\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161218\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221553563009\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196418\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Slverfox94739\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/25/2019 at 9:16 PM, Slverfox94739 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I don\u0027t use\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003EKronometer is does go to a 24 our clock. But the Sun\u00A0sets and rises 3 times during\u00A0that period (SSRSS has a ~8 hour day). I know it\u00A0just cosmetic, But I was trying to find a way use the 24 hour colck but only have the Sun rise/set once.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre you saying you want to the clock to show that 24 hours elapse during the 8-hour rotation period of the planet?\u00A0 If so, then yes, Kronometer can do that.\u00A0 You can find the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/StollD/Kronometer\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E Kronometer syntax on GitHub\u003C/a\u003E.\u00A0 I think you might need to do something like this, which redefines the length of an hour to be 1200 seconds, or 20 minutes.\u00A0 That way the clock will click off 24 hours in one day.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E@Kronometer:AFTER[SSRSS]\n{\n\t@CustomTime\n\t{\n\t\t@Hour\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tvalue = 1200\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I\u0027ve misunderstood and you actually want to change the rotation period of the planet to 24 hours, then that\u0027s not a Kronometer issue.\u00A0 You can\u0027t do that by writing a Kopernicus config.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-11T15:14:52Z\u0022 title=\u002203/11/2020 03:14  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 11, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by OhioBob\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Slverfox94739","CreatedById":196418,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-26T07:18:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks OhioBob that is what I was looking for.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OhioBob","CreatedById":128005,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-27T03:45:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223568995\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161218\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221553584725\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196418\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Slverfox94739\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, Slverfox94739 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks OhioBob that is what I was looking for.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerhaps it would be even better to also redefine a minute to be 20 seconds long.\u00A0 That way a day will have 24 hours and an hour will have 60 minutes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E@Kronometer:AFTER[SSRSS]\n{\n\t@CustomTime\n\t{\n\t\t@Hour\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tvalue = 1200\n\t\t}\n\t\t@Minute\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tvalue = 20\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dave1904","CreatedById":153882,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-10T17:53:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNever used it before but using this with rescale 2x5 seems to work perfectly on 1.8.1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-10T17:56:46Z\u0022 title=\u002203/10/2020 05:56  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 10, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by dave1904\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Useless_useR","CreatedById":199919,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-14T19:36:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood day. I am using a 2.5 scale system and am using this mod. Dawn starts at about 5.20am and the day changes when the sun is high. But in real life, the day changes at night. Is it possible to somehow adjust the clock so that day changes to night?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OhioBob","CreatedById":128005,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-15T04:50:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223838113\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161218\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221597433799\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022199919\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Useless_useR\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, Useless_useR said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood day. I am using a 2.5 scale system and am using this mod. Dawn starts at about 5.20am and the day changes when the sun is high. But in real life, the day changes at night. Is it possible to somehow adjust the clock so that day changes to night?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerhaps the best way to change that is to edit the initial rotation of the planet.\u00A0 Assuming you\u0027re playing stock Kerbin, give this a try...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E@Kopernicus:FINAL\n{\n\t@Body[Kerbin]\n\t{\n\t\t@Properties\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tinitialRotation = 220\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI haven\u0027t tested this, so I don\u0027t know if that rotation is correct.\u00A0 I just estimated it assuming we have 6-hours days and we want to move sunrise from 5:20 to 1:30.\u00A0 If it\u0027s not right you can tweak it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E(Kerbin\u0027s default initialRotation = 90)\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-08-15T04:55:32Z\u0022 title=\u002208/15/2020 04:55  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 15, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by OhioBob\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}